<html><head><title>Headway - April 1996 &quot;The magazine for today's political leaders&quot;</title></head><body>
<center><H2>April's Contents</h2><b>Vol. 8, No. 4</b><p><hr><p></center>


COVER STORY: DEMOCRATS: THE STATUS QUO PARTY<br>
              <ul><li>Democrats' Policies Lead To Nation's Complacency by Brian W. Jones<br>
              <li>Reports of Democrats' Demise Are Greatly Exaggerated by Bill Maxwell<br>
              <li>Democratic Party Needs to Promote Success Principles by Angela W. Harper<br>
</ul><p>
</ul>
THE NATION:  COMMENTARIES ON NATIONAL ISSUES
<UL>  <li>            Too Many Students Lack Academic Motivation by Elwood Watson
              <li>Choosing The Next Leader Of The Free World by Errol Smith
              <li>The High Cost of Wrong-Headed Predictions by Walter E. Williams 
              <li>Random Thoughts On The Passing Scene by Thomas Sowell 
              <li>Group Rights Lobby Blocks School Choice by Peter Kirsanow
              <li>Will Republicans' Plan To Revitalize Inner Cities Succeed? by Robert Stanton
              <li>American Can and Should Legislate Family Values by Willie and Gwen Daye Richardson 
              <li>Bring Back The Stigma On Teenage Pregnancy by Joseph H. Brown 
              <li>Is There A "Cultural War" In America? by Ezola Foster
</ul>     

FEATURES
<ul>
     <li>WILL CHILE'S SLOW LEFTWARD DRIFT IMPERIL ITS GAINS?
     by Deroy Murdock Congressional District, Connecticut
     <li>PULSE OF THE POLLS
              Political Attitudes Of Black Americans
     <li>SPEAKING OUT: Tearing Up The Race Card by Camille Harper<p>
</ul>


