<body>
<center><h2>SEPTEMBER CONTENTS</h2><p>
<b>Vol. 7, No. 9<p>
September 1995</b></center><P><hr><P>

<ul>
<B><LI>COVER STORY<BR>
HOLLYWOOD STEREOTYPES:</B> How Hollywood Typecasts Blacks, Families, and Christians<br>
<ul><LI>Modern-Day Minstrel Shows by Stanley Crouch<br>
<li>Movies Too Often Portray Christians As Fanatics by Gary L. Bauer<br></ul>
<p><B><li>THE NATION: COMMENTARIES ON NATIONAL ISSUES</B><BR>
<UL><LI>Constitution Doesn't Prohibit Prayer In Public Schools by Linda Chavez<br>
<li>Racism Is Racism, For Pete's Sake by Ezola Foster<br>
<li>Stumbling Into Hell In The Balkans by Thomas Sowell<br>
<li>Real-Life Impact of Americans With Disabilities Act by Walter E. Williams<br>
<li>Is America Ready To Be Fair? by Sidney Hill<br>
<li>A Bird's Eye View of the Nigerian Economy by Deborah Burstion-Donbraye<br>
<li>Is There Life After Preferences? by Errol Smith<br>
<li>Get Off The Bus And Start Walking Toward The Future by Joseph H. Brown<br>
