<p><img src="bullet.gif" hspace=5 height=14 width=14 align=top>
April
18, 1996</p>

<p>

<ul>
<p><img src="diamond.gif" hspace=5  vspace="4" height=14 width=14 align=top><b><a href="http://khht.com/huber/home.html">Testimony
before the Subcommittee on Government Management</a>
</b><br> By Peter Huber, FCC Working
Group Member
<br></p>
</ul>

<p><img src="bullet.gif" hspace=5 height=14 width=14 align=top>
April
11, 1996</p>

<p>

<ul>
<p><img src="diamond.gif" hspace=5 vspace="4" height=14 width=14 align=top><b><a href="http://www.pff.org/pff/censor.html">An
E-Burst on Dow's Place: The future of Censorship
</b><br></a>By Michael Vlahos.
<br></p>
</ul>

<p><img src="bullet.gif" hspace=5 height=14 width=14 align=top>
April
2, 1996</p>

<p>

<ul>
<p><img src="diamond.gif" hspace=5  vspace="4" height=14 width=14 align=top><b><a href="http://www.pff.org/pff/cad/ct0401b.html">Testimony
on the Federal Communications Commission</a>

